9996 <h2>Choosing the Perfect Pendant Lighting for Your Home&nbsp;</h2>

9997 <p>&nbsp;</p>

9998 <p>Pendant lights are the jewelry of your home, hung in areas where you want the style of a light fixture to support an interior design while providing functional or ambient lighting. As such, they are most often installed over kitchen islands, dining tables, and entryway foyers. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

9999

Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 9999 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h2>&nbsp;</h2>

10000 <h2>Types of Pendant Styles</h2>

10001 <ul>

10002 <li>Traditional</li>

10003 <li>Modern</li>

10004 <li>Contemporary</li>

10005 <li>Farmhouse</li>

10006 <li>Rustic</li>

10007 <li>Industrial</li>

10008 <li>LED</li>

10009 <li>Lantern</li>

10010 </ul>

10011 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10012 <p>Choosing the right pendants for your home depends on what you want to achieve. Are you looking for task lighting, ambient lighting, accent lighting, or decorative lighting? Whatever you choose, we have the pendant lights to fit your home.</p>

10013

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10013 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h2>&nbsp;</h2>

10014 <h2>What is a Pendant Light?</h2>

10015 <p>Sometimes called drop lighting or suspended lighting, pendant lights hang from the ceiling from a chain, cord, or rod. And since they are generally small, pendants are typically installed in tandem with other pendant lights, unless its a linear pendant a hanging light fixture with multiple lights spread out horizontally along a frame and often installed over billiard tables.&nbsp;</p>

10016 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10017 <p>Pendant lights are mostly installed over kitchen islands, wet bars, foyers, and hallways with vaulted ceilings. And while some pendant lamps certainly provide mood lighting, most are designed to have functional coverage with a striking style the light fixture is meant to support an interiors design ethos, after all.&nbsp;</p>

10018 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10019 <p>If a pendant light is not what youre looking for, here are other

10020 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling/">ceiling lights</a> to consider:

10021 </p>

10022 <ul>

10023 <li>

10024 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-chandeliers/">Chandeliers</a>: A hanging light, like a pendant, but with branching arms of lights, traditional chandeliers are typically larger than pendants, and installed by themselves in places where they become the focal point of a room. Often decorative and opulent, crystal chandeliers are a traditional type of chandelier youd find in a ballroom.

10025 </li>

10026 <li>

10027 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-flush-mounts/">Flush Mounts</a>: A ceiling light where the fixture is flush to the ceiling. Flush mounts often utilize dome-shaped shades and are installed in the middle of a room for functional lighting. A semi-flush mount is like a cross between a pendant and a flush mount. It hangs close to the ceiling from a short rod, but it usually has the same shapes as a flush mount, often utilizing drum shades. The short distance between the light fixture and the ceiling often creates interesting shadows on the ceiling.

10028 </li>

10029 <li>

10030 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-recessed/">Recessed Lights</a>: A ceiling light built into the ceiling. Recessed lights are all about functionality, which makes them popular, especially in homes with low ceilings. Its popular to pair recessed lights with pendants to brighten a room.

10031 </li>

10032 <li>

10033 <a href="https://vevano.com/catalog/fans-ceiling-with-lights/">Ceiling Fans with Lights</a>: Often placed in bedrooms or living rooms, this is a ceiling light attached to a fan. While fandeliers combine the austere style of a chandelier with a fan, most ceiling fans with lights are simple, yet functional.

10034 </li>

10035 </ul>

10036

<h2>&nbsp;</h2>

10037 <h2>Expanded: Pendant Light Styles</h2>

10038 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10039 <p>Most interior lighting design types have broad definitions. Some have roots in historical eras, such as modern, traditional, and farmhouse. Others are specific takes on broader styles, such as industrial style being a type of modern style. The relative ambiguity of interior lighting design provides room for you to express yourself and find the home within your house.&nbsp;</p>

10040

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10040 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10041 <h3>Modern Pendant Lighting</h3>

10042 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10043 <p>Reaching peak popularity in the 20th century, modern design is defined by a bias towards minimalism. And modern pendant lights are no different. The shape of the frame and shade is clean. Its striking, but in a simple 1950s sort of way globe pendants, drum shades, clear glass shades, polished nickel fixtures, square metal frames, bold solid colors like white and black.&nbsp;</p>

10044 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10045 <p>Modern pendant lamps arent decorative for the sake of being decorative. Rather, modern pendants prioritize functionality over form. But that doesnt mean they arent stylish. Theres a reason why modern design is still very popular after nearly a century it feels inviting and accessible, clean and elegant, hip and fun.</p>

10046

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10046 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10047 <h3>Contemporary Pendant Lighting</h3>

10048 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10049 <p>Often confused with modern style (because modern and contemporary have very similar meanings), a contemporary pendant light is whats new in design trends right now. As such, contemporary pendant lights often differ a great deal from modern pendant lights, which refers to a specific era during the 20th century. If you want a futuristic hanging lamp or a polished chrome hanging light in line with current trends, then a contemporary design is what youre looking for.&nbsp;</p>

10050 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10051 <p>Current contemporary trends include asymmetrical designs, lights built with integrated LEDs, lots of clear glass, experimental glass textures (like bubbles), orb shapes, globes, and smart technology.</p>

10052

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10052 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10053 <h3>Farmhouse Pendant Lighting</h3>

10054 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10055 <p>The farmhouse style is a type of modern style, as it focuses on simple designs and minimalism. However, a farmhouse pendant light focuses more on warmth and coziness by using natural materials and textures like hand-blown glass, die-cast iron, weathered wood, polished nickel, brass, copper, or a combination of natural materials. And while farmhouse pendants are mostly modern in their design, they often include minor embellishments.&nbsp;</p>

10056 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10057 <p>The most popular farmhouse pendant lamps feature a wood drum shade frame with steel parts, such as joists. And the light bulbs are typically Edison style bulbs with vintage shapes. Matte black and oil-rubbed bronze finishes are also popular with farmhouse pendants. When using a farmhouse light, use a bulb with a color temperature below 3000 kelvins to emphasize the warm and cozy atmosphere.</p>

10058

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10058 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10059 <h3>Rustic Pendant Lighting</h3>

10060 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10061 <p>A rustic style pendant relies on weathered materials to provide an antiqued look. Rustic is often paired with farmhouse to create a rustic farmhouse style, which uses the same modern minimalism and natural materials of a farmhouse style, but in an aged, lived-in motif with more antiques or second-hand dcor.&nbsp;</p>

10062 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10063 <p>However, rustic style isnt just applied to modern farmhouse styles. You can apply the rustic ethos to other styles as well. For example, a rustic traditional style features the same decorative embellishments of traditional styles, but with a purposeful patina that adds to the antique look. For example, an antique copper pedant light in a Victorian lantern style, but with discoloration in the copper.&nbsp;</p>

10064

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10064 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10065 <h3>Industrial Pendant Lighting</h3>

10066 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10067 <p>Industrial style is a type of early modern style that focuses on the raw minimalism of simple, yet functional shapes. The style emphasizes the textures and colors of raw materials, often incorporating die-cast metals, unfinished wood, brass, copper, and antique glass.&nbsp;</p>

10068 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10069 <p>As such, industrial pendant lighting fixtures often looks like it was pulled from an early 20th century textile factory. Its simple, yet unrefined. Often, the fixture combines weathered wood with iron bars and braces, not unlike a rustic style. For example, the die-cast iron fixture is often pitted and worn with an Edison bulb. Sometimes the bulb is surrounded by a thin wire frame instead of a shade.&nbsp;</p>

10070

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10070 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10071 <h3>LED Pendant Lighting</h3>

10072 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10073 <p>LED pendant light isnt a style, but a lighting fixture that uses integrated LED lights. Typically, these are common in contemporary mini-pendant lights, since its relatively new technology thats much smaller than other bulbs. However, regardless of the style, choosing an LED pendant light has many advantages.&nbsp;</p>

10074 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10075 <p>LED bulbs use far less energy than an incandescent or Xenon bulbs. As such, you pay less money on energy bills over the life of the bulb. And speaking of life, an LED bulb last many times longer than other bulbs. And since LEDs last longer and can be much smaller, contemporary designs have gotten more experimental, often using integrated LEDs because they know the light can last well over a decade.&nbsp;</p>

10076

Headings should not be empty.

<h3>&nbsp;</h3>

10077 <h3>Lantern Pendant Lighting</h3>

10078 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10079 <p>Sometimes referred to as hanging lanterns or hanging lamps, lantern pendant lighting draws its design from the basic shape of a traditional gas or candle lantern a boxy shaped frame with glass shades and incandescent candelabra bulbs. While the classic lantern lamp pendant is firmly part of a traditional style, the lantern shape has its place in all types of styles, even contemporary and industrial, which have simplified the shape into its most basic proportions.</p>

10080 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10081 <p>The popular lantern pendant style right now features a simple metal frame welded in the lantern shape around a core of lights hanging from a chain. The frame is taller than it is wide and often wider at the top than the bottom with the top frame angled towards a point where it meets the chain or rod. Most of these types of metal-frame lanterns fall within contemporary and modern styles. If it uses weathered wood in the frame, its an excellent fit into rustic or farmhouse style.&nbsp;</p>

10082

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10082 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h2>&nbsp;</h2>

10083 <h2>Choosing the Function</h2>

10084 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10085 <p>Pendant lights are meant to be seen, which is why finding a style you like is important. However, pendants need to be functional too. Here are the four types of functionality to consider before choosing a pendant light:</p>

10086 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10087 <p>

10088 <strong>Task Lighting</strong>

10089 <br>These pendants are all about bright and clear illumination of the space below. If you use your kitchen island to cook and other tasks, look for pendants with the bulb aimed downwards. The best task-lighting pendants have closed frames with an open bottom, allowing the light to only light the surface below. As such, task lighting doesnt light the room.&nbsp;

10090 </p>

10091 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10092 <p>Incorporate a dimmer switch to adjust the brightness. You may not want the bright task lighting when youre done cutting vegetables.&nbsp;</p>

10093 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10094 <p>

10095 <strong>Ambient Lighting</strong>

10096 <br>Ambient pendant lights are meant to light up a room rather than a specific area. This makes them ideal for foyers, over dining tables, or hallways with tall ceilings. The frame is open, allowing the light to disperse in all directions. And the shade is often stylized to create a specific mood.&nbsp;

10097 </p>

10098 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10099 <p>Ambient pendant lighting should never be harsh. Rather, you want to achieve a pleasant glow, relying on warm lights and shades that soften the light. Dimmers are also great for adjusting the glow to match your mood.</p>

10100 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10101 <p>

10102 <strong>Accent Lighting</strong>

10103 <br>For accent lighting, youre focused on highlighting specific items or areas in your home, such as a painting, a unique architectural point of focus, or a reading nook. While sconces, track lighting, and lamps are popular choices for accent lights, pendant lights work well for certain conditions, such as highlighting a countertop made of an exotic material, such as a charoite stone with iridescent streaks or wild agate countertops with fossils.&nbsp;

10104 </p>

10105 <p>You want to make sure the light highlights the beauty of the material without being too harsh. As such, finding mini-pendant lights somewhere between task and ambient lighting is ideal downward lighting, but with a soft glow.</p>

10106 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10107 <p>

10108 <strong>Decorative Lighting</strong>

10109 <br>With decorative lighting, the pendants style is the focus. Think about it as being a functional art piece Youre choosing the pendant fixtures based more on how it looks in the room, how it supports the rooms overall dcor, how it catches the eye. The functionality of the light is still important, but its secondary.

10110 </p>

10111 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10112 <p>Decorative lighting fixtures also incorporate interesting shadows, both on the ceiling and throughout the room. They typically rely on textured shades and up/down lighting. &nbsp;</p>

10113

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.
Line 10113 WCAG 2.1 AA G130 Section 508 (2017) AA G130

<h2>&nbsp;</h2>

10114 <h2>FAQs About Pendant Lighting</h2>

10115 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10116 <p>

10117 <strong>Whats the right pendant light size?</strong>

10118 <br>There isnt a right rule for choosing the right size pendant light fixtures, but most expert designers recommend breaking the area into fourths and finding an equal ratio by adding the length and width of the area and converting it to inches. This formula finds both the correct ratio for three pendant light fixtures but also accounts for the correct spacing. For example, for a 5-foot by 3-foot kitchen island, youd have three pendant lights with an 8 diameter separated by 15 increments.

10119 </p>

10120 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10121 <p>

10122 <strong>Where should I put a pendant light?</strong>

10123 <br>Pendant lights are most often placed above islands and bars. Foyers and hallways are also popular areas for pendants, especially with vaulted ceilings.&nbsp;

10124 </p>

10125 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10126 <p>

10127 <strong>How to install a pendant light?</strong>

10128 <br>Installing a pendant light is relatively simple if the junction box is already in place. You only need a few tools screwdriver, wire cutters, voltmeter, short ladder. If youre installing the pendant in a new location, the process becomes far more complicated, as it involves cutting a hole in the ceiling and getting the electrical wires to the new location.

10129 </p>

10130 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10131 <p>Any time youre dealing with electricity, consider hiring a professional electrician. It may add costs to a project, but no pendant light is worth the shock you may receive if you dont take safety precautions or the potential fire hazards if wiring isnt done correctly. &nbsp;</p>

10132 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10133 <p>That said, the basic steps of installing a new pendant in an old location are:</p>

10134 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10135 <ol>

10136 <li>

10137 <em>Safety first:</em> Turn off the power at the homes main circuit box and cover the switch with tape to keep someone from accidentally turning the power back on while youre working. Also, remove the shade and bulb from the pendant so that when youre hanging the fixture, you minimize the risk of damaging anything, especially glass.&nbsp;

10138 </li>

10139 <li>

10140 <em>Prepare the junction box:</em> Once the old light is removed, there should be three wires two for power and a ground. Using a voltmeter, make sure the power is off by touching it to the wires. If there isnt a reading, you know its safe. Now you can remove any mounting brackets for the previous light.&nbsp;

10141 </li>

10142 <li>

10143 <em>Attach Mounting Brackets:</em> Using the screwdriver, mount the new mounting bracket and make sure its sturdy. The cord attaches to the mounting bracket.&nbsp;

10144 </li>

10145 <li>

10146 <em>Adjust the Length:</em> Before you hang the pendant, adjust the length of the chain or cord. With cords, you typically do this by pulling the cord through the ceiling plate until it reaches the desired length and tightening a screw to hold it in place. The addition cord will be tucked into the junction box.&nbsp;

10147 </li>

10148 <li>

10149 <em>Attach the Wire:</em> Twist the wires from the cord to the two wires, and cap them with wire nuts, ensuring there arent any excess wires spilling out of the wire nut. Screw the ground wire into the mounting bracket. Let the pendant hang to make sure its at the desired length.

10150 </li>

10151 <li>

10152 <em>Attach the cover:</em>Make sure the junction box is covered up by the pendants cover plate.

10153 </li>

10154 <li>

10155 <em>Add Shades and Bulbs:</em>With the fixture hang, add the shade and bulb.

10156 </li>

10157 <li>

10158 <em>Turn on the Power:</em>Turn the power back on and turn the light on to see how it looks.

10159 </li>

10160 </ol>

10161 <p>

10162 <br>

10163 <strong>How much light will a pendant provide?</strong>

10164 <br>The amount of light depends on the lumens of the bulb used in the lighting, the direction of the light, and the type of shade. If the shade is clear glass and open, you can expect a wide coverage in all areas. But many pendants are designed to aim the light down with enough coverage to provide great visibility below, but not enough light to illuminate an entire room.

10165 </p>

10166 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10167 <p>

10168 <strong>How far apart should you place pendant lights?</strong>

10169 <br>The general recommendation is to place pendant lights 30 apart. This is enough space to keep the pendants away from each other while being close enough for the light coverage to overlap. However, the exact spacing is not as important as uniform spacing. Make sure the spacing is equal from pendant to pendant.

10170 </p>

10171 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10172 <p>

10173 <strong>Can you replace recessed lighting with pendant lighting?</strong>

10174 <br>Yes! With recessed lighting, the junction box is already in place. You simply need to make sure your pendants ceiling plate covers the hole and make sure the pendant comes with a mounting bracket. If it doesnt, you can purchase a conversion kit, which usually costs about $15 to $20 for a mounting bracket and trim pieces.

10175 </p>

10176 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10177 <p>

10178 <strong>What is the difference between a chandelier and pendant?</strong>

10179 <br>Chandelier and pendants are both light fixtures that hang from the ceiling and both can be extremely stylistic and ambient. And while some styles of pendants blur the line between pendant and chandelier, to the point where some large pendants are described as chandelier pendants and some mini-chandeliers are called pendant chandeliers, the difference lies primarily in the size and purpose.&nbsp;

10180 </p>

10181 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10182 <p>Pendant light fixtures are usually smaller and used in both functional and stylistic installations while chandeliers are generally wider, taller, and the focal point of a room. Chandeliers also rely on a branch system that moves out from a center and holds the primary lights towards the edge. On the other hands, pendants display the light in more types of ways, though its most often downward lighting.</p>

10183 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10184 <p>

10185 <strong>What are pendant lights used for?</strong>

10186 <br>Pendant lights are often used to light a bar area or a kitchen island. As such, the lighting fixtures are usually downward so that it clearly illuminates the countertop below. However, pendants are also used in foyers and hallways and can be omnidirectional lighting.

10187 </p>

10188 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10189 <p>

10190 <strong>How do you choose the right size pendant light?</strong>

10191 <br>Start by considering the area you want to illuminate and the room youre placing the pendant fixtures in. If youre lighting a kitchen island, you want pendant lights with enough coverage for the entire island. This could be many small pendants or a few large pendants.&nbsp;

10192 </p>

10193 <p>&nbsp;</p>

10194 <p>

10195 <strong>How do you adjust a pendant light?</strong>

10196 <br>Most pendant lights hang from cords. To adjust the length, you need to get a stepladder and loosen a screw on the ceiling plate. This should allow the cord to move. If there is excess cord in the junction box, loosening the screw lets the pendant drop, so its important you hold on to the cord. If you want to make it shorter, you simply need to push the cord into the junction box until you reach the desired length, then tighten the screw.&nbsp;

10197 </p>

10198

Headings should not be empty.
Add text to the heading, or alt text if the heading contains an image. Screen readers read out page headings, allowing users to quickly skip to a section, but some older screen readers do not ignore empty headings.

10368"css":"","html":"\u003ch2\u003eChoosing the Perfect Pendant Lighting for Your Home\u0026nbsp;

10369\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10370\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePendant lights are the jewelry of your home, hung in areas where you want the style of a light fixture to support an interior design while providing functional or ambient lighting. As such, they are most often installed over kitchen islands, dining tables, and entryway foyers. \u0026nbsp;

10371\u0026nbsp;

10372\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10373\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eTypes of Pendant Styles\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eTraditional\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eModern\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eContemporary\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eFarmhouse\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eRustic\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eIndustrial\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLED\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003eLantern\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10374\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eChoosing the right pendants for your home depends on what you want to achieve. Are you looking for task lighting, ambient lighting, accent lighting, or decorative lighting? Whatever you choose, we have the pendant lights to fit your home.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10375\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eWhat is a Pendant Light?\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSometimes called drop lighting or suspended lighting, pendant lights hang from the ceiling from a chain, cord, or rod. And since they are generally small, pendants are typically installed in tandem with other pendant lights, unless it\u0026rsquo;

10376s a linear pendant \u0026ndash;

10377 a hanging light fixture with multiple lights spread out horizontally along a frame and often installed over billiard tables.\u0026nbsp;

10378\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10379\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePendant lights are mostly installed over kitchen islands, wet bars, foyers, and hallways with vaulted ceilings. And while some pendant lamps certainly provide mood lighting, most are designed to have functional coverage with a striking style \u0026ndash;

10380 the light fixture is meant to support an interior\u0026rsquo;

10381s design ethos, after all.\u0026nbsp;

10382\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10383\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIf a pendant light is not what you\u0026rsquo;

10384re looking for, here are other \u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling/\"\u003eceiling lights\u003c/a\u003e to consider:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-chandeliers/\"\u003eChandeliers\u003c/a\u003e: A hanging light, like a pendant, but with branching arms of lights, traditional chandeliers are typically larger than pendants, and installed by themselves in places where they become the focal point of a room. Often decorative and opulent, crystal chandeliers are a traditional type of chandelier you\u0026rsquo;

10385d find in a ballroom.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-flush-mounts/\"\u003eFlush Mounts\u003c/a\u003e: A ceiling light where the fixture is flush to the ceiling. Flush mounts often utilize dome-shaped shades and are installed in the middle of a room for functional lighting. A semi-flush mount is like a cross between a pendant and a flush mount. It hangs close to the ceiling from a short rod, but it usually has the same shapes as a flush mount, often utilizing drum shades. The short distance between the light fixture and the ceiling often creates interesting shadows on the ceiling.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/lighting-ceiling-recessed/\"\u003eRecessed Lights\u003c/a\u003e: A ceiling light built into the ceiling. Recessed lights are all about functionality, which makes them popular, especially in homes with low ceilings. It\u0026rsquo;

10386s popular to pair recessed lights with pendants to brighten a room.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://vevano.com/catalog/fans-ceiling-with-lights/\"\u003eCeiling Fans with Lights\u003c/a\u003e: Often placed in bedrooms or living rooms, this is a ceiling light attached to a fan. While fandeliers combine the austere style of a chandelier with a fan, most ceiling fans with lights are simple, yet functional.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10387\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eExpanded: Pendant Light Styles\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10388\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eMost interior lighting design types have broad definitions. Some have roots in historical eras, such as modern, traditional, and farmhouse. Others are specific takes on broader styles, such as industrial style being a type of modern style. The relative ambiguity of interior lighting design provides room for you to express yourself and find the home within your house.\u0026nbsp;

10389\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10390\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eModern Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10391\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eReaching peak popularity in the 20th century, modern design is defined by a bias towards minimalism. And modern pendant lights are no different. The shape of the frame and shade is clean. It\u0026rsquo;

10392s striking, but in a simple 1950\u0026rsquo;

10393s sort of way \u0026ndash;

10394 globe pendants, drum shades, clear glass shades, polished nickel fixtures, square metal frames, bold solid colors like white and black.\u0026nbsp;

10395\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10396\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eModern pendant lamps aren\u0026rsquo;

10397t decorative for the sake of being decorative. Rather, modern pendants prioritize functionality over form. But that doesn\u0026rsquo;

10398t mean they aren\u0026rsquo;

10399t stylish. There\u0026rsquo;

10400s a reason why modern design is still very popular after nearly a century \u0026ndash;

10401 it feels inviting and accessible, clean and elegant, hip and fun.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10402\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eContemporary Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10403\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eOften confused with modern style (because \u0026ldquo;

10404modern\u0026rdquo;

10405 and \u0026ldquo;

10406contemporary\u0026rdquo;

10407 have very similar meanings), a contemporary pendant light is what\u0026rsquo;

10408s new in design trends right now. As such, contemporary pendant lights often differ a great deal from modern pendant lights, which refers to a specific era during the 20th century. If you want a futuristic hanging lamp or a polished chrome hanging light in line with current trends, then a contemporary design is what you\u0026rsquo;

10409re looking for.\u0026nbsp;

10410\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10411\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eCurrent contemporary trends include asymmetrical designs, lights built with integrated LEDs, lots of clear glass, experimental glass textures (like bubbles), orb shapes, globes, and smart technology.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10412\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eFarmhouse Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10413\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe farmhouse style is a type of modern style, as it focuses on simple designs and minimalism. However, a farmhouse pendant light focuses more on warmth and coziness by using natural materials and textures like hand-blown glass, die-cast iron, weathered wood, polished nickel, brass, copper, or a combination of natural materials. And while farmhouse pendants are mostly modern in their design, they often include minor embellishments.\u0026nbsp;

10414\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10415\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe most popular farmhouse pendant lamps feature a wood drum shade frame with steel parts, such as joists. And the light bulbs are typically Edison style bulbs with vintage shapes. Matte black and oil-rubbed bronze finishes are also popular with farmhouse pendants. When using a farmhouse light, use a bulb with a color temperature below 3000 kelvins to emphasize the warm and cozy atmosphere.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10416\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eRustic Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10417\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eA rustic style pendant relies on weathered materials to provide an antiqued look. Rustic is often paired with farmhouse to create a rustic farmhouse style, which uses the same modern minimalism and natural materials of a farmhouse style, but in an aged, lived-in motif with more antiques or second-hand d\u0026eacute;

10418cor.\u0026nbsp;

10419\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10420\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eHowever, rustic style isn\u0026rsquo;

10421t just applied to modern farmhouse styles. You can apply the rustic ethos to other styles as well. For example, a rustic traditional style features the same decorative embellishments of traditional styles, but with a purposeful patina that adds to the antique look. For example, an antique copper pedant light in a Victorian lantern style, but with discoloration in the copper.\u0026nbsp;

10422\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10423\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eIndustrial Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10424\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIndustrial style is a type of early modern style that focuses on the raw minimalism of simple, yet functional shapes. The style emphasizes the textures and colors of raw materials, often incorporating die-cast metals, unfinished wood, brass, copper, and antique glass.\u0026nbsp;

10425\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10426\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs such, industrial pendant lighting fixtures often looks like it was pulled from an early 20th century textile factory. It\u0026rsquo;

10427s simple, yet unrefined. Often, the fixture combines weathered wood with iron bars and braces, not unlike a rustic style. For example, the die-cast iron fixture is often pitted and worn with an Edison bulb. Sometimes the bulb is surrounded by a thin wire frame instead of a shade.\u0026nbsp;

10428\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10429\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eLED Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10430\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLED pendant light isn\u0026rsquo;

10431t a style, but a lighting fixture that uses integrated LED lights. Typically, these are common in contemporary mini-pendant lights, since it\u0026rsquo;

10432s relatively new technology that\u0026rsquo;

10433s much smaller than other bulbs. However, regardless of the style, choosing an LED pendant light has many advantages.\u0026nbsp;

10434\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10435\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eLED bulbs use far less energy than an incandescent or Xenon bulbs. As such, you pay less money on energy bills over the life of the bulb. And speaking of life, an LED bulb last many times longer than other bulbs. And since LEDs last longer and can be much smaller, contemporary designs have gotten more experimental, often using integrated LEDs because they know the light can last well over a decade.\u0026nbsp;

10436\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10437\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003eLantern Pendant Lighting\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10438\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eSometimes referred to as hanging lanterns or hanging lamps, lantern pendant lighting draws its design from the basic shape of a traditional gas or candle lantern \u0026ndash;

10439 a boxy shaped frame with glass shades and incandescent candelabra bulbs. While the classic lantern lamp pendant is firmly part of a traditional style, the lantern shape has its place in all types of styles, even contemporary and industrial, which have simplified the shape into its most basic proportions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10440\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThe popular lantern pendant style right now features a simple metal frame welded in the lantern shape around a core of lights hanging from a chain. The frame is taller than it is wide and often wider at the top than the bottom with the top frame angled towards a point where it meets the chain or rod. Most of these types of metal-frame lanterns fall within contemporary and modern styles. If it uses weathered wood in the frame, it\u0026rsquo;

10441s an excellent fit into rustic or farmhouse style.\u0026nbsp;

10442\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10443\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eChoosing the Function\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10444\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePendant lights are meant to be seen, which is why finding a style you like is important. However, pendants need to be functional too. Here are the four types of functionality to consider before choosing a pendant light:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10445\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTask Lighting\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nThese pendants are all about bright and clear illumination of the space below. If you use your kitchen island to cook and other tasks, look for pendants with the bulb aimed downwards. The best task-lighting pendants have closed frames with an open bottom, allowing the light to only light the surface below. As such, task lighting doesn\u0026rsquo;

10446t light the room.\u0026nbsp;

10447\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10448\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIncorporate a dimmer switch to adjust the brightness. You may not want the bright task lighting when you\u0026rsquo;

10449re done cutting vegetables.\u0026nbsp;

10450\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10451\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAmbient Lighting\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nAmbient pendant lights are meant to light up a room rather than a specific area. This makes them ideal for foyers, over dining tables, or hallways with tall ceilings. The frame is open, allowing the light to disperse in all directions. And the shade is often stylized to create a specific mood.\u0026nbsp;

10452\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10453\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAmbient pendant lighting should never be harsh. Rather, you want to achieve a pleasant glow, relying on warm lights and shades that soften the light. Dimmers are also great for adjusting the glow to match your mood.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10454\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAccent Lighting\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nFor accent lighting, you\u0026rsquo;

10455re focused on highlighting specific items or areas in your home, such as a painting, a unique architectural point of focus, or a reading nook. While sconces, track lighting, and lamps are popular choices for accent lights, pendant lights work well for certain conditions, such as highlighting a countertop made of an exotic material, such as a charoite stone with iridescent streaks or wild agate countertops with fossils.\u0026nbsp;

10456\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eYou want to make sure the light highlights the beauty of the material without being too harsh. As such, finding mini-pendant lights somewhere between task and ambient lighting is ideal \u0026ndash;

10457 downward lighting, but with a soft glow.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10458\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eDecorative Lighting\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nWith decorative lighting, the pendant\u0026rsquo;

10459s style is the focus. Think about it as being a functional art piece \u0026ndash;

10460 You\u0026rsquo;

10461re choosing the pendant fixtures based more on how it looks in the room, how it supports the room\u0026rsquo;

10462s overall d\u0026eacute;

10463cor, how it catches the eye. The functionality of the light is still important, but it\u0026rsquo;

10464s secondary.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10465\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eDecorative lighting fixtures also incorporate interesting shadows, both on the ceiling and throughout the room. They typically rely on textured shades and up/down lighting. \u0026nbsp;

10466\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10467\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eFAQs About Pendant Lighting\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10468\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat\u0026rsquo;

10469s the right pendant light size?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nThere isn\u0026rsquo;

10470t a right rule for choosing the right size pendant light fixtures, but most expert designers recommend breaking the area into fourths and finding an equal ratio by adding the length and width of the area and converting it to inches. This formula finds both the correct ratio for three pendant light fixtures but also accounts for the correct spacing. For example, for a 5-foot by 3-foot kitchen island, you\u0026rsquo;

10471d have three pendant lights with an 8\u0026rdquo;

10472 diameter separated by 15\u0026rdquo;

10473 increments.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10474\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhere should I put a pendant light?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nPendant lights are most often placed above islands and bars. Foyers and hallways are also popular areas for pendants, especially with vaulted ceilings.\u0026nbsp;

10475\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10476\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow to install a pendant light?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nInstalling a pendant light is relatively simple if the junction box is already in place. You only need a few tools \u0026ndash;

10477 screwdriver, wire cutters, voltmeter, short ladder. If you\u0026rsquo;

10478re installing the pendant in a new location, the process becomes far more complicated, as it involves cutting a hole in the ceiling and getting the electrical wires to the new location.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10479\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAny time you\u0026rsquo;

10480re dealing with electricity, consider hiring a professional electrician. It may add costs to a project, but no pendant light is worth the shock you may receive if you don\u0026rsquo;

10481t take safety precautions or the potential fire hazards if wiring isn\u0026rsquo;

10482t done correctly. \u0026nbsp;

10483\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10484\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat said, the basic steps of installing a new pendant in an old location are:\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10485\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003col\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eSafety first:\u003c/em\u003e Turn off the power at the home\u0026rsquo;

10486s main circuit box and cover the switch with tape to keep someone from accidentally turning the power back on while you\u0026rsquo;

10487re working. Also, remove the shade and bulb from the pendant so that when you\u0026rsquo;

10488re hanging the fixture, you minimize the risk of damaging anything, especially glass.\u0026nbsp;

10489\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003ePrepare the junction box:\u003c/em\u003e Once the old light is removed, there should be three wires \u0026ndash;

10490 two for power and a ground. Using a voltmeter, make sure the power is off by touching it to the wires. If there isn\u0026rsquo;

10491t a reading, you know it\u0026rsquo;

10492s safe. Now you can remove any mounting brackets for the previous light.\u0026nbsp;

10493\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAttach Mounting Brackets:\u003c/em\u003e Using the screwdriver, mount the new mounting bracket and make sure it\u0026rsquo;

10494s sturdy. The cord attaches to the mounting bracket.\u0026nbsp;

10495\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAdjust the Length:\u003c/em\u003e Before you hang the pendant, adjust the length of the chain or cord. With cords, you typically do this by pulling the cord through the ceiling plate until it reaches the desired length and tightening a screw to hold it in place. The addition cord will be tucked into the junction box.\u0026nbsp;

10496\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAttach the Wire:\u003c/em\u003e Twist the wires from the cord to the two wires, and cap them with wire nuts, ensuring there aren\u0026rsquo;

10497t any excess wires spilling out of the wire nut. Screw the ground wire into the mounting bracket. Let the pendant hang to make sure it\u0026rsquo;

10498s at the desired length.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAttach the cover: \u003c/em\u003eMake sure the junction box is covered up by the pendant\u0026rsquo;

10499s cover plate.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eAdd Shades and Bulbs: \u003c/em\u003eWith the fixture hang, add the shade and bulb.\u003c/li\u003e\n\t\u003cli\u003e\u003cem\u003eTurn on the Power: \u003c/em\u003eTurn the power back on and turn the light on to see how it looks.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\n\u003cstrong\u003eHow much light will a pendant provide?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nThe amount of light depends on the lumens of the bulb used in the lighting, the direction of the light, and the type of shade. If the shade is clear glass and open, you can expect a wide coverage in all areas. But many pendants are designed to aim the light down with enough coverage to provide great visibility below, but not enough light to illuminate an entire room.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10500\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow far apart should you place pendant lights?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nThe general recommendation is to place pendant lights 30\u0026rdquo;

10501 apart. This is enough space to keep the pendants away from each other while being close enough for the light coverage to overlap. However, the exact spacing is not as important as uniform spacing. Make sure the spacing is equal from pendant to pendant.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10502\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCan you replace recessed lighting with pendant lighting?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nYes! With recessed lighting, the junction box is already in place. You simply need to make sure your pendant\u0026rsquo;

10503s ceiling plate covers the hole and make sure the pendant comes with a mounting bracket. If it doesn\u0026rsquo;

10504t, you can purchase a conversion kit, which usually costs about $15 to $20 for a mounting bracket and trim pieces.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10505\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat is the difference between a chandelier and pendant?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nChandelier and pendants are both light fixtures that hang from the ceiling and both can be extremely stylistic and ambient. And while some styles of pendants blur the line between pendant and chandelier, to the point where some large pendants are described as \u0026ldquo;

10506chandelier pendants\u0026rdquo;

10507 and some mini-chandeliers are called \u0026ldquo;

10508pendant chandeliers,\u0026rdquo;

10509 the difference lies primarily in the size and purpose.\u0026nbsp;

10510\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10511\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003ePendant light fixtures are usually smaller and used in both functional and stylistic installations while chandeliers are generally wider, taller, and the focal point of a room. Chandeliers also rely on a branch system that moves out from a center and holds the primary lights towards the edge. On the other hands, pendants display the light in more types of ways, though it\u0026rsquo;

10512s most often downward lighting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10513\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWhat are pendant lights used for?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nPendant lights are often used to light a bar area or a kitchen island. As such, the lighting fixtures are usually downward so that it clearly illuminates the countertop below. However, pendants are also used in foyers and hallways and can be omnidirectional lighting.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10514\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you choose the right size pendant light?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nStart by considering the area you want to illuminate and the room you\u0026rsquo;

10515re placing the pendant fixtures in. If you\u0026rsquo;

10516re lighting a kitchen island, you want pendant lights with enough coverage for the entire island. This could be many small pendants or a few large pendants.\u0026nbsp;

10517\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10518\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eHow do you adjust a pendant light?\u003c/strong\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\nMost pendant lights hang from cords. To adjust the length, you need to get a stepladder and loosen a screw on the ceiling plate. This should allow the cord to move. If there is excess cord in the junction box, loosening the screw lets the pendant drop, so it\u0026rsquo;

10519s important you hold on to the cord. If you want to make it shorter, you simply need to push the cord into the junction box until you reach the desired length, then tighten the screw.\u0026nbsp;

10520\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10521\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003ch2\u003eDo Your Pendants Hang Low? Choose the Best Pendant Lights at Vevano\u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u0026nbsp;

10523t need to be an overwhelming experience. Whether you\u0026rsquo;

10524re looking for modern style task lights or contemporary ambient lighting, we have the best pendant light brands at Vevano.\u0026nbsp;
